VMS Short Term Income Trust said itagreed to commit to fund a 1.8 mln dlrs loan increase for 1420K Street, a 12-story, 60,000 square foot office building inWashington, D.C.    The trust previously approved a 2.9 mln dlr loan for theproperty, making the total loan 4.7 mln dlrs.    VMS said the increased financing will have an initial termof six months and will include a one pct participation in thenet appreciation of the property upon sale or refinancing. Reuter&#3;